<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-03-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="373" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Dawson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-03-17"><hi rend="italic">March 17,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your telegram of March 16, 5 p.m., received. You may informally express
                            to President Reyes our cordial sympathy and our confidence that he will
                            do all possible to bring about the approval of the treaties, and thus
                            consummate the good relationship we so earnestly desire.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>